{"cursor":"25584","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Linguistic anthropology' is the interdisciplinary study of how language\ninfluences social life. It is a branch of anthropology that originated from the\nendeavor to document endangered languages, and has grown over the past 100 years\nto encompass almost any aspect of language structure and use. Duranti, Alessandro. ed. 2004.\n[http://books.google.com/books?id=3jMmmQjssaEC Companion to Linguistic\nAnthropology]. Malden, MA: Blackwell.\n\nLinguistic anthropology explores how language shapes communication, forms social\nidentity and group membership, organizes large-scale cultural beliefs and\nideologies, and develops a common cultural representation of natural and social\nworlds. Society for Linguistic Anthropology. n.d.\n[http://www.linguisticanthropology.org/about/ About the Society for Linguistic\nAnthropology.] Accessed 7 July 2010.\n","linknr":387,"url":"Linguistic_anthropology","recorded":1362480886,"links":25,"instances":["paranormal","social_science","linguistic_anthropologist","personal_and_cultural"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Anthropology","Applied linguistics"],"headings":["Historical development","Areas of interest","See also","References","Further reading","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Da_Vinci_Vitruve_Luc_Viatour.jpg/180px-Da_Vinci_Vitruve_Luc_Viatour.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Moai_Easter_Island_InvMH-35-61-1.jpg/10px-Moai_Easter_Island_InvMH-35-61-1.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["value","personal_and_cultural"],["magic","paranormal"],["identity","social_science"],["miyako_inoue","linguistic_anthropologist"]],"members":["magic","identity","miyako_inoue","value"],"related":["Interdisciplinarity","An